1. Follow current coding best practices.
2. Write clear, descriptive code comments.
3. Use meaningful variable names that clearly indicate their purpose.
4. Document your code with concise, easy-to-understand explanations.
5. Implement comprehensive error handling with user-friendly messages.
6. Design an intuitive and modern user interface.
7. Optimize code for performance and fast loading times.
8. Edit code files sequentially, not simultaneously.
9. When replacing code, clearly specify both the original and new code.
10. Use CDN for dependencies, frameworks, and libraries unless specified otherwise.